<p>SoX <a href="http://sox.sourceforge.net/sox.html#:~:text=Out%20Of%20Phase%20Stereo%20effect.">Oops</a>.</p>

<p>If output is 0 then both channels are probably exactly the same, so track is dual-mono, if output is 1 then at some point in track there is no similarity at all, probably â€˜stereoâ€™ or two different tracks muxed. So â€˜Maximum amplitudeâ€™ could be renamed to â€˜Max diff between channelsâ€™ or similar.</p>

<p>A very simple, maybe useful <a href="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/brontosaurusrex/bucentaur/master/.experiments/bin/oops">oops-loop-script</a>.</p>

<p>Conclusion: No, this is way to simple to answer the <em>isStereo</em> question.</p>
